\n| `running_cost_nn1e6/config.json` | Legacy model dir | NO | NO | — | None |\n| `figures/baseline_jerk_vrnn_matrix__variance_profiles/` | Figure dir | NO | — | YES (references results/part2_5/runs/ run.jsons by relative path) | Not yet (_artifacts/part2_5/figures/ doesn't exist) |\n| `runpod/anti_anticipation_loss_shape_6cell/` | Experiment dir (runpod in path — **violation**) | YES | 6 run.json (inside runs/) | 5 spec.json (inside figures/) | YES (_artifacts/part2_5/runpod/anti_anticipation_loss_shape_6cell/) |\n| `runpod/anti_anticipation_prereg_3cell/` | Stub (RUN_PLAN.md only) | NO | NO | — | None |\n| `runpod/anti_anticipation_test/` | Stub (RUN_PLAN.md only) | NO | NO | — | None |\n| `runpod/baseline_jerk_vrnn_matrix/` | Experiment dir (runpod in path — **violation**) | NO (has RESULTS.md instead) | NO — runs migrated to runs/ flat dir | — | YES (_artifacts/part2_5/runpod/baseline_jerk_vrnn_matrix/) |\n| `runpod/baseline_smoothness/standard_12k_smooth/` | Stub — extra nesting level | NO | NO | — | None |\n| `flavor_b_README.md` | Floating narrative doc | — | — | — | — |\n| `synthesis_review.md` | Long-form post-mortem | — | — | — | — |\n| `peak_velocity_flavor_b/cross_method_comparison.md` | Analysis narrative | NO | NO | — | None |\n| `induced_gain_flavor_b/cross_method_comparison.md` | Analysis narrative | NO | NO | — | None |\n| `runs/` (20 flat dirs) | New-style run specs | — | YES (30 total) | — | Partial (flavor_b refs _artifacts/part2_5/runpod/flavor_b/ which does not exist locally) |\n\n### _artifacts/ experiments with NO results/ mirror (unregistered runs)\n\nAll 11 are under _artifacts/part2_5/runpod/:\n\n| Dir | Contents |\n|---|---|\n| `baseline/standard_12k/` | Warmup-only GRU baseline, config.json |\n| `bench/bs5000_proc{1-4}/` | Throughput benchmark runs |\n| `minimax_single/seed_{0-4}/` | Minimax adversarial training, 5 seeds |\n| `mult_pop5/`, `mult_single/` | APT-style population vs single runs |\n| `ratio03_pop5/`, `ratio03_single/` | Ratio=0.3 runs |\n| `ratio_sweep/` (16 cells) | r∈{0.2,0.5} × arch × pert × pop sweep |\n| `tier1_redo/` (8 cells) | r=0.3 re-runs |\n| `vanilla_pop5/`, `vanilla_single/` | Vanilla runs |\n\nThese all have config.json but no run.json in results/. Per post-training-run protocol (CLAUDE.md §9) these should have received spec commit on a feature branch. They did not.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Anomaly Audit\n\n| # | Anomaly | Severity | Affected paths |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| A1 | **Cloud-provider dir in results/** | High | `results/part2_5/runpod/*` (5 experiment dirs) |\n| A2 | **_artifacts runs with no results/ spec** | High | 11 dir groups under _artifacts/part2_5/runpod/ |\n| A3 | **config.json instead of run.json** (legacy) | Medium | 22 dirs in `models/`, 4 `centerout_*/`, 1 `running_cost_nn1e6`, top-level `part2_5/config.json` |\n| A4 | **Experiment dirs missing README.md** | Medium | centerout_* (4), part2_5/models/* (22), part2_5/runpod/baseline_jerk_vrnn_matrix |\n| A5 | **run.json input_artifact path does not resolve** | Medium | `runs/flavor_b_*/run.json` references `_artifacts/part2_5/runpod/flavor_b/` which is absent locally; `runs/induced_gain_flavor_b/run.json` has absolute worktree path |\n| A6 | **552+ PNGs in results/** exceeding 300 KB thumbnail limit | Medium | `1_general.assets/` (52 oversize), `2_general.assets/` (similar) — notebook-embedded figures violating artifact policy |\n| A7 | **Floating narrative docs** without experiment home | Low | `part2_5/flavor_b_README.md`, `part2_5/synthesis_review.md` (these are good content but sit as siblings to experiment dirs) |\n| A8 | **Stub dirs** with only RUN_PLAN.md, no run artifacts | Low | `runpod/anti_anticipation_prereg_3cell/`, `runpod/anti_anticipation_test/`, `runpod/baseline_smoothness/standard_12k_smooth/` |\n| A9 | **RESULTS.md instead of README.md** | Low | `runpod/baseline_jerk_vrnn_matrix/` |\n| A10 | **flavor_a_vs_b has no _artifacts mirror** | Low | `results/flavor_a_vs_b/` — expected _artifacts/flavor_a_vs_b/ does not exist |\n| A11 | **anti_anticipation_smoke has no _artifacts mirror** | Low | `results/anti_anticipation_smoke/` — expected _artifacts/anti_anticipation_smoke/ does not exist |\n| A12 | **Inconsistent run-spec conventions within part2_5** | Low | Old-style: `runpod/\u003cexp\u003e/runs/\u003cvar\u003e/run.json`; New-style: `runs/\u003cexp\u003e__\u003cvar\u003e/run.json` — two patterns coexist |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Reorganization Proposal\n\n### 3a. Flat vs Nested vs Hybrid (answering the user's question)\n\n**Flat-by-hash** is recommended.\n\nArguments:\n- The user has already converged on this: \"I'm going to develop a system where results will be easily reviewed with respect to the issue... in that case we don't have to worry about this.\" When Mandible/Studio surfaces human-readable framing by issue ID, directory names are purely for filesystem plumbing.\n- Nested-by-phase adds one indirection level that helps no one: phase membership is already captured in issue bodies and the b33e8da coord. Directory depth should not replicate issue graph relationships.\n- Flat-by-hash is already the convention for branches (`feature/2bc95fd__anti-anticipation-6cell`-style branches derive from issue IDs). Aligning results/ to this makes the mapping obvious.\n- The only real argument for nesting is \"ls results/ shows 60 hashes\" — addressed by Mandible Studio or a simple `mandible issue list` overlay.\n\n**Proposal: `results/\u003c7-char-issue-id\u003e/`** as the single structural unit. Within it:\n\n\n\nNo phase-level parent dir. Phase membership is tracked in b33e8da via comments; the issue itself carries the umbrella link in its body.\n\n**What about the 1_general.md / 2_general.md notebooks?** These are phase-level artifacts, not experiment-level. They belong under the phase umbrella issue: `results/0af472c/1_general.md` (Part 2 umbrella) and their .assets/ dirs alongside. Their embedded PNGs \u003e 300 KB should migrate to _artifacts/ and be symlinked.\n\n**Run identifier stays** `\u003cgroup\u003e__\u003cvariant\u003e` (double underscore), matching branch convention.\n\n### 3b. Concrete Mapping: Current → Proposed\n\n| Current | Proposed | Migration type |\n|---|---|---|\n| `results/part2_5/` | `results/part2_5/` (keep; it is a well-formed phase artifact dir with README.md) | **Keep as-is** — it pre-dates hash-based convention and is large enough to justify an exception; link in b33e8da |\n| `results/part2_5/runpod/anti_anticipation_loss_shape_6cell/` | `results/2bc95fd/` | Rename (strip runpod/) |\n| `results/part2_5/runpod/baseline_jerk_vrnn_matrix/` | Merge into `results/efc4d68/` (the baseline matrix issue) | Rename + merge RESULTS.md → README.md |\n| `results/part2_5/runs/baseline_jerk_vrnn_matrix__*/` | `results/efc4d68/runs/\u003cgroup\u003e__\u003cvariant\u003e/` | Move |\n| `results/part2_5/figures/baseline_jerk_vrnn_matrix__variance_profiles/` | `results/efc4d68/figures/variance_profiles/` | Move |\n| `results/part2_5/runpod/anti_anticipation_prereg_3cell/` | Archive or delete — only RUN_PLAN.md; run superseded by 6cell | Delete stub |\n| `results/part2_5/runpod/anti_anticipation_test/` | Archive or delete — stub only | Delete stub |\n| `results/part2_5/runpod/baseline_smoothness/` | Create `results/\u003cissue-id-for-baseline-smoothness\u003e/` when that issue is found | Deferred |\n| `results/anti_anticipation_smoke/` | `results/efc4d68/smoke/` or keep at top-level with README pointing to efc4d68 | Minor move |\n| `results/flavor_a_vs_b/` | Keep as-is — it is cross-cutting synthesis, not an experiment dir | Keep |\n| `results/centerout_apt_pert1/` (+ 3 siblings) | `results/part2_5/models/centerout_apt_pert1/` (consolidate with legacy models) | Consolidate into part2_5 legacy block |\n| `results/part2_5/models/` (22 dirs) | Keep as legacy block; add single-line README.md to parent | Keep |\n| `results/1_general.md` + `.assets/` | `results/0af472c/1_general.md` + assets | Move under Part 2 umbrella |\n| `results/2_general.md` etc. | `results/0af472c/2_general.md` + assets | Move under Part 2 umbrella |\n| `results/brainstorming_network.md` | `results/0af472c/brainstorming_network.md` or delete (uncertain provenance) | Deferred |\n| `results/part2_5/peak_velocity_flavor_b/` | `results/part2_5/runs/peak_velocity_flavor_b/` (it has companion run.json already there) | Consolidate |\n| `results/part2_5/induced_gain_flavor_b/` | Merge into `results/part2_5/runs/induced_gain_flavor_b/` (run.json sibling) | Merge |\n| `results/part2_5/flavor_b_README.md` | Move into `results/part2_5/runs/` parent as context note, or into flavor_a_vs_b/ | Move |\n| Unregistered _artifacts runs (11 dirs) | Create `results/\u003cissue-id\u003e/runs/\u003cgroup\u003e__\u003cvariant\u003e/run.json` for each | **Priority fix** (post-training-run protocol violation) |\n\n### 3c. The NP-hard part: unregistered _artifacts runs\n\nThese 11 dirs need to be traced to their tracking issues before run.json can be written. Candidates:\n- `baseline/standard_12k` → probably efc4d68 or a new baseline issue\n- `minimax_single/seed_{0-4}` → the minimax tracking issue (not found in issue list above; may be c723082 or a separate issue)\n- `bench/bs5000_proc{1-4}` → throughput benchmarks; probably 76d3a8e or cdfc132\n- `mult_*/`, `ratio*`, `tier1_redo/`, `vanilla_*/` → Part 2.5 APT sweeps from the original phase; likely 0af472c umbrella children\n\nThis archaeology is a separate task, flagged here for the orchestrator to assign.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Symlink Rollout Bundling (0f1af24)\n\n**Sequence: reorg first, then symlink in one pass.**\n\nAfter reorg:\n1. For each `results/\u003cid\u003e/runs/\u003cgroup\u003e__\u003cvariant\u003e/`, create `_artifacts/\u003cid\u003e/runs/\u003cgroup\u003e__\u003cvariant\u003e/` as the mirror (if it doesn't exist).\n2. For each `results/\u003cid\u003e/figures/\u003cfig\u003e/`, symlink any files in the corresponding `_artifacts/\u003cid\u003e/figures/\u003cfig\u003e/` back into results/.\n3. Gate condition: only symlink when _artifacts counterpart exists locally. Dangling symlinks are acceptable for cloud-run artifacts not yet rsync'd back, but each dangling symlink must have a companion run.json that records what the artifact path should be.\n4. .gitignore treatment: symlinks themselves should be **tracked** (tiny text, signals expectation). The targets are already gitignored via _artifacts/ wildcard.\n\nSimplest atomic operation: write a small `wt-sync-artifacts.sh` script (analog to wt-sync) that reads a `results/\u003cid\u003e/_artifacts_map.yaml` (or infers from run.json `input_artifacts` fields) and creates/updates the symlinks. Run it after every rsync-back from a cloud pod.\n\n---\n\n## 5. CLAUDE.md Convention Additions\n\nThe reorg implies two new convention entries, to be filed as a follow-up update:\n\n1. **results/ root structure**: \"Each experiment or analysis group in results/ is a directory named by its 7-char issue-ID prefix (e.g., results/2bc95fd/). Phase-level artifacts (notebooks, narratives) live under the phase umbrella's issue-ID dir. The legacy results/part2_5/ exception is grandfathered; new work does not add phase-named dirs.\"\n\n2. **Symlink convention (from 0f1af24)**: \"After rsync-back from a cloud pod, run wt-sync-artifacts to create symlinks from results/\u003cid\u003e/figures/\u003cfig\u003e/\u003cfile\u003e → _artifacts/\u003cid\u003e/figures/\u003cfig\u003e/\u003cfile\u003e. Tracked symlinks are allowed in results/; their targets are gitignored.\"\n\n---\n\n*Cross-ref: 0f1af24 (symlink rollout, bundle with this reorg). The two issues should be implemented together in a single feature branch.*","files":null}]}